==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pent
<hw>Pent</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>p. p. ⟦or⟧ a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Pen</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>Penned or shut up; confined;
-- often with <xex>up</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here in the body <qex>pent</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Montgomery.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No <qex>pent-up</qex> Utica contracts your powers.</q> <rj><qau>J.
M. Sewall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pent-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: pent-
<hw>pent-</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>pref.</pos> <def>Same as
<er>penta-</er>; -- used as a combining form before vowels, as in
<ex>pent</ex>oxide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penta-</ent>⟦br⟧
